import { Button } from "@material-ui/core";
import React, { useContext } from "react";
import "./dashbord.css";
import Grid from "@material-ui/core/Grid";
import NewContext from './newContex';

const NewButton = () => {
  const context = useContext(NewContext);

  return (
        <Grid
          item
          xs={12}
          className="literals"
          container
          direction="row"
          justify="flex-start"
          alignItems="flex-start"
        >
          <Grid item xs={2} className="part1">
            <Button  value={context.operatorValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>
            +
            </Button>
            <Button value={context.operatorValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>
              -
            </Button>
            <Button value={context.operatorValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>
              *
            </Button>
            <Button value={context.operatorValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>
              =
            </Button>
          </Grid>
          <Grid item xs={2} className="part1">
            <Button value={context.operatorValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>
              /
            </Button>
            <Button value={context.operatorValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>
              %
            </Button>
            <Button value={context.operatorValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>
            x²
            </Button>
            <Button value={context.operatorValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>
            √
            </Button>
          </Grid>
          <Grid item xs={8} className="part2">
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>1</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>2</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>3</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>4</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>5</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>6</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>7</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>8</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>9</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>0</Button>
            <Button value={context.numberValue} onClick={context.handelClick}>.</Button>
          </Grid>
        </Grid>
  );
};
NewButton.propTypes = {
  fullname :PropTypes.string,
  handelClick :PropTypes.func,
};
export default NewButton;
